title Local fork Pass 1 — urbit/vere restructure, keys, PDT convention
prompt Kaeden asked to clone groupproject36/veganreyklah2 into a local ~/urbit fork layered over urbit/urbit and urbit/vere histories, generate a fresh identity (keatondun@gmail.com) with ed25519 SSH+GPG keys for the xykj61 forges, adapt the project's time convention to Pacific (Reno, NV) for this local clone, and hold the harder Rye-OS-on-macOS and Azimuth/Comlink design work for a second pass after reading the project's own docs.
think Read SOURCE.md, context/RIO3.md, context/TAME_GUIDANCE.md, .claude/rules/session-logs.md, .claude/rules/git-signing.md, .claude/rules/collaboration.md, work-in-progress/ROADMAP.md before touching any files — this project is a mature, already-running Rye OS with dozens of live modules, not a green field, so the Rye-reimplementation half of the original ask needed rescoping.
think Found ~/urbit already occupied by an unrelated Oct-2025 personal collection (nockchain, urbit.org, an old urbit/urbit clone) — paused and asked Kaeden how to handle it rather than overwrite silently; Kaeden chose to nest all three inside the new old/ directory.
think Mirror-backed up urbit/urbit and urbit/vere to ~/backups/ before any destructive move, since global ~/.gitconfig rewrites https to ssh and no SSH key existed yet for plain github.com auth — worked around by temporarily renaming ~/.gitconfig during the anonymous clones.
think Rebuilt ~/urbit as: fresh urbit/urbit .git history at top level, veganreyklah2 working tree moved to the top level in its place, old/ holding the original urbit/urbit files plus the three legacy Oct-2025 clones. vere follows the requested variant — its own .git relocated to ~/.git-vere-backup/ (outside ~/urbit entirely) so ~/urbit/vere is tracked only by the parent project's history going forward.
think Generated a clean ed25519 identity for keatondun@gmail.com — id_ed25519_urbit_github, id_ed25519_urbit_codeberg, and one GPG signing key (fpr 1622 6BC7 D5B3 1C88 8809 2BE6 F096 19B9 B845 1F67) — leaving the three pre-existing unrelated GPG identities on this machine untouched.
think Configured ~/urbit's local git config (not global) with the new identity, signing key, and a core.sshCommand pinned to the two new keys, since the global ~/.ssh/config host aliases for github.com/codeberg.org already belong to a different identity (kaexvx9) that should not be disturbed.
think Started gh auth login (device flow) for the xykj61 GitHub account as a detached background job after the first attempt died with its parent shell; Kaeden completes the browser step since that credential exchange cannot be done by the agent.
think Reno, NV observes Pacific Time (PDT in summer, UTC-8 in winter as PST) — the upstream one-clock naming law names no timezone at all, so this stamp and this log establish Pacific as the explicit local-clone convention rather than leaving it ambiguous.
obs The Rye OS "reimplement urbit and vere" ask is not a from-scratch design task — the project already has Rye, Caravan, Brushstroke, Rishi, Mantra, Comlink, Tablecloth, Brix, Bron, Tally, Aurora, Pond, and an active Linengrow product track with hundreds of landed witnesses. Pass 2 should scope SOURCE.md's macOS/ai-jail adaptation, QEMU-vs-Virtualization.framework research, and Azimuth/Comlink design against that existing shape, not against a blank page.
obs SOURCE.md's ai-jail install line targets cargo/Nix on Linux; macOS has no bwrap/Landlock equivalent, so the sandbox story needs real adaptation (Seatbelt/sandbox-exec, or accepting a lighter boundary) before Pass 2 can respect "safety first."
file ~/urbit/.gitignore why: added !/old/ and !/vere/ to the allow-list, plus a macOS Finder/Spotlight/AppleDouble ignore family beside the existing .DS_Store line (Linux host had named only that one).
file ~/urbit/PUBKEYS_new/ why: holds the exported public GPG armor and both new SSH public keys for Kaeden to paste into GitHub/Codeberg account settings; left outside the allow-list on purpose, so it is never tracked.
file ~/backups/urbit-mirror.git why: full bare mirror of urbit/urbit, taken before any local deletion, as the safety net Kaeden asked for.
file ~/backups/vere-mirror.git why: full bare mirror of urbit/vere, same reasoning.
file ~/.git-vere-backup/ why: vere's original .git history, moved outside ~/urbit per Kaeden's explicit variant for vere (unlike urbit/urbit, whose .git stays inside the project).
recommend check-in with Kaeden before Pass 2 — the Rye-OS-on-macOS sandbox adaptation, the Azimuth contract address confirmation, and the vere issue migration all cross a design seam (host-OS security boundary, an external contract address that must be verified fresh, and an irreversible GitHub-API write against someone else's issue tracker) that no written policy in this tree answers yet.
